title: Strictly's Saffron Barker leaves hotel with Katya Jones and Oti Mabuse ahead of the second live show
text:
She is set to Paso Doble to Lorde's Everybody Wants To Rule The World with her professional dance partner AJ Pritchard on Saturday's Strictly Come Dancing.

And ahead of the second live show, Saffron Barker was pictured leaving her hotel and heading to the studio alongside Katya Jones and Oti Mabuse.

The YouTube star, 19, appeared in high spirits as she stepped out wearing a black tracksuit with a graphic emblem on the chest.

Heading home: Saffron Barker was pictured leaving her hotel and heading to the studio alongside Katya Jones and Oti Mabuse

She layered the look with a distressed black leather jacket and a pair of chunky white Alexander McQueen trainers with a panel of black on the heels of the shoe.

Saffron wore her blonde locks in a straight blown out style, and opted for a natural coat of make-up in neutral shades to complete her look.

The Brighton native carried her belongings in a black shoulder bag, while carrying other items in a Jo Malone carrier bag.

Casual: Meanwhile, Oti also opted for a casual look as she wore a grey jumper and a sequin-encrusted black denim jacket with a pair of ribbed charcoal joggers

Glam: Katya put on a chic display as she headed out of the hotel wearing a black trench coat, which was belted around the waist in neat bow

Meanwhile, Oti also opted for a casual look as she wore a grey jumper and a sequin-encrusted black denim jacket with a pair of ribbed charcoal joggers.

Showcasing her naturally radiant complexion, the professional dancer went make-up free and wore her ombre tresses in a loose and flowing style.

She added a pair of red glasses and white trainers to complete her look.

Glowing: Saffron wore her blonde locks in a straight blown out style, and opted for a natural coat of make-up in neutral shades to complete her look

Coffee break: Janette Manrara looked chic in a camel waterfall jacket as she sipped coffee

Katya put on a chic display as she headed out of the hotel wearing a black trench coat, which was belted around the waist in neat bow.

She styled her locks in a sleek top knot and opted for a glamorous coat of make-up including a bold cherry red lip, which complemented her bright red T-shirt.

The Russian dancer added an edgy vibe to her look with a pair of chunky lace-up boots, which also featured straps across the front.

Stepping out: Kelvin Fletcher looked casual in a black tracksuit while Giovanni Pernice cut a sharp figure in a shirt and pinstriped trousers

The songs and dances for Strictly Come Dancing: Movie Week have finally be revealed, with some of the show's most hilarious combinations to date.

Among the highlights are Mike Bushell, who will embrace Channing Tatum with a Cha Cha Cha to It's Raining Men from Magic Mike.

Will Bayley will also deliver a Paso Doble to the Pokemon theme tune, and Michelle Visage is set to dance a Quickstep to Liza Minelli's Cabaret.

Following the elimination of James Cracknell on Saturday the remaining 14 couples will take to the dancefloor for the much-anticipated Movie Week Special.

Ab-flashing: Amy Dowden flashed her midriff in a leopard print crop top

Mike is certainly expected to be a highlight, as he takes on Tatum's role of Magic Mike in the 2012 film to The Weather Girls' It's Raining Men.

The breakfast presenter will take to the floor with Katya Jones after finishing close to the bottom of the leaderboard last week.

Will's dance is certainly an unusual choice, as he is set to dance the Paso Doble to Jason Paige's version of the Pokemon theme titled Gotta Catch 'Em All.

He will take to the floor with Janette Manrara after wowing the judges with his Samba last week.

Casual: AJ rocked bright red tracksuit bottoms and an Iron Maiden T-shirt

Catherine Tyldesley will take to the floor with pro Johannes Radebe to dance a sensual rumba to Shallow from A Star Is Born.

After ending up in the dance-off last week, David James and Nadiya Bychkova will be aiming to bounce back with an American Smooth (Viennese Waltz) to Seal's chart-topping hit Kiss From A Rose in Batman Forever.

Emma Weymouth and Aljaž Škorjanec will embrace her Viscountess title with a Foxtrot to the Downton Abbey theme tune, and Saffron Barker will also take on the paso doble with AJ Pritchard to Lorde's Everybody Wants To Rule The World from The Hunger Games.

Michelle Visage will embrace her inner showgirl with a fast-paced Quickstep alongside Giovanni Pernice, to the legendary Liza Minelli song Cabaret.

Anneka Rice and Kevin Clifton will perform a Charleston to Woo Hoo from Kill Bill, while Alex Scott and Neil Jones will dance a romantic Rumba to Moana's How Far I'll Go.

Strictly Come Dancing: Movie Week airs on Saturday at 7:10pm on BBC One
